class Solution:
    def findDelayedArrivalTime(self, arrivalTime: int, delayedTime: int) -> int:
        return (arrivalTime + delayedTime) % 24
```

This solution calculates the delayed arrival time by adding the `arrivalTime` and `delayedTime` and then uses the modulo operator to ensure the time is within the 24-hour format. If the sum is 24 or more, it wraps around to the start of the day.
